A former gubernatorial aspirant and Chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Osun State, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi, has exited himself from the party. Ogunbiyi who took the action via a resignation letter addressed to Iyorchia Ayu the party national chairman, appreciated the PDP family for the “interaction and engagements within the party over the years.” Contents of the letter read thus: “Please accept this letter as a formal resignation from the PDP with effect from 28th March 2022.” It will be recalled that, few hours to the contest for the party gubernatorial primary election,Dr Akin Ogunbiyi announced his pulling out from the race. The party chieftain made his withdrawal known at his campaign office in Ogo-oluwa,area of Osogbo, the state capital While stating while he withdrew from the race, he argued that, there was a conspiratorial plan by the leadership of the party from the national headquarters to be bias in the election. Ogunbiyi further pointed out that, the Adeleke camp has equally perfected plans to molest, harass and even caused mayhem that could claim the lives of his political supporters during the party primary election. ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
